title: The Great Forest Park Bicycle Race
Power and Light Family Fun Ride
Velo Force Short Track Dirt Crit Series
Kansas City Cup Cross
description:
360 Racing has a great new venue to christen within the city limits of Kansas City. This is the 1st race of Series 60 Cyclocross, a local 7 race series within Kansas City Metro area (www.series60cx.com/),and the 1st CX race in the Kansas City area. The race will occur at the Camp Lake of the Woods in Swope Park, a never before used venue. This race will be part of the Kansas City Cup Race Festival Weekend, with mountain bike racing on Sunday, Sept 20th. Come for the cross race on Saturday and stay for the MTB race on Sunday.A portion of the proceeds of both races will be donated to the Swope trail network and ERTA.
Check out www.heartlandrace.com for festival information.
course: The course will be available for pre-riding after 10:00 on raceday.
registration: Pre-registration available at the Wednesday night Boulevard cyclocross training series. Race day registration available at 9:30. Registration for each event closes 30 minutes before the posted start times. Cost: $25/race, $10/jrs. & 2nd race
notes: All USCF rules apply. USCF license required to race all USCF categories. One-day USCF licenses available for $10.00. Event held rain or shine. ANSI approved helmets required at all times while on a moving bicycle. Fee includes $3 for USCF insurance and $1 for KCA surcharge. No cash payout will exceed $499 for any category. Contact Ted Moore @moore166@hotmail.com for additional info
directions:
From the West: From 71 HWY, head east on East Gregory Blvd. to Oldham Road (right/east). Turn right on Oldham Road. Go apx. 1 mile to Oakwood Drive entrance (Camp Lake of the Woods). Turn left. Follow the signs for parking at the top of the hill.
From the East: From I-435. Gregory Blvd exit. Head west apx. 2 miles to Oldham Road (just past Lake of the Woods.) Turn Left. Go apx. 1 mile to Oakwood Drive entrance (Camp Lake of the Woods). Turn left. Follow the signs for parking at the top of the hill.
